cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on the security of passwords and the effectiveness of guessing attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of personal information in password cracking, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper proposes a novel password cracker based on Markov models, which involves machine learning techniques and could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
